commit.message:
Fix resource leak

1). File handles from fopen should be closed by fclose after use.
    Free fil_handle in the function doIn after reading date from each file.

2). Memory allocated from xcmalloc/xcrealloc should be freed after use.
    Free file_names in the function doIn after reading data from all files.
Merge change to default to -o (output mode) when stdin is a tty.
Merge branch 'sensiblestdin' of https://github.com/hackerb9/xclip into hackerb9-sensiblestdin

commit.message: Use xcnamestr for more succinct code

ICCCM 2.1 says XSetSelectionOwner may "merely appear to succeed"

So, double-check by using XGetSelectionOwner().
try multiple sizes of binary data, up to 16MB

When losing selection, print name of new owner

Make normal exit not look like an error.

Remove superfluous redundancy

Add --debug, cleanup and shorten help

Make it fit on an 80x24 character terminal.
Also, reorder the options so that similar features are grouped
and the most important ones come first.
replace calls printing ID number with xcnamestr

Add xcnamestr convenience function

Show window id # in parens after name

Author: b9 <hackerb9@member.fsf.org>
Date:   Wed Sep 30 06:34:11 2020 -0700

    Explicitly state how to compile 'borked'

    Apparently, gcc for 32-bit Linux requires libraries (-lX11 -lXmu)
    to come AFTER the object and source files. Using the implicit
    rule works fine on 64-bit Linux, but with the same version of gcc (8.3)
    and autoconf (2.69), it barfs with "Undefined reference to XFree", etc.
